@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - analytics/AnalyticsInstance
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired AnalyticsInstance spec, tracked\nstatus, and delete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via\nGetAnalyticsInstance;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListAnalyticsInstances using filters\ncapacityType, compartmentId, featureSet, name;
:Create the OCI resource via\nCreateAnalyticsInstance when no reusable match\nis found;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path uses DeleteAnalyticsInstance with\nrequired via GetAnalyticsInstance or\nListAnalyticsInstances to DELETED confirmation;
:Confirm deletion via GetAnalyticsInstance or\nListAnalyticsInstances until OCI reaches\nDELETED;
if ("Delete cleanup and finalizer release succeed?") then (yes)
:Remove the finalizer after delete completion;
else (no)
:Stay blocked until cleanup or finalizer\nrelease succeeds;
endif
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state in retryable set?") then (yes)
:Request requeue while OCI remains in CREATING,\nUPDATING, DELETING;
stop
endif
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE, INACTIVE;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the\nrepo-authored mutation surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields capacity.capacityType, featureSet,\nname,\nnetworkEndpointDetails.networkEndpointType;
stop
endif
if ("Supported mutable drift detected?") then (yes)
:Apply ChangeAnalyticsInstanceCompartment,\nChangeAnalyticsInstanceNetworkEndpoint,\nScaleAnalyticsInstance (+3 more) only for\nmutable fields definedTags, description,\nemailNotification, freeformTags (+2 more);
else (no)
:Skip the no-op mutation path;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource when the\nmatching field-driven path executes;
:Return success for the ACTIVE, INACTIVE\nsuccess state;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nretain-until-confirmed-delete;
:Requeue on provisioning, updating, terminating;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: analytics
slug: analyticsinstance
kind: AnalyticsInstance
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update
UPDATING; delete DELETING
supported drift: definedTags, description,
emailNotification, freeformTags (+2 more)
reject before mutate: force-new fields
capacity.capacityType, featureSet, name,
networkEndpointDetails.networkEndpointType
create-only fields: adminUser, domainId,
idcsAccessToken
list lookup: oci_analytics_analytics_instances
filters capacityType, compartmentId, featureSet,
name; exact compartmentId plus name plus
featureSet plus capacityType unique match in
ACTIVE, CREATING, UPDATING, or INACTIVE;
duplicate matches fail
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, UPDATING as updating, ACTIVE and
INACTIVE as success, and DELETING as
terminating; FAILED is terminal and DELETED is
only a delete-confirmation target.
Create and delete responses expose work-request
headers, while UpdateAnalyticsInstance returns
only opc-request-id plus the resource body. The
runtime records shared async breadcrumbs from
lifecycle projection rather than polling
GetWorkRequest directly.
Only description, emailNotification,
licenseType, freeformTags, definedTags, and
updateChannel reconcile in place. FeatureBundle
and KmsKeyId stay in required status projection,
but supporting SetFeatureBundle or SetKmsKey
remains out of scope for the published runtime.
DomainId remains a create-time input that is
read back into status. AdminUser and
IdcsAccessToken are create-time inputs OCI does
not echo back, so they are normalized out of
post-create parity checks.
Required status projection keeps
NetworkEndpointDetails, PrivateAccessChannels,
VanityUrlDetails, updateChannel, featureBundle,
domainId, and systemTags on the published kind,
and the runtime has no secret side effects.
end note
@enduml
